        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 7 at 5:25PM PDT by NWS Pendleton OR</headline>
        <description>At 525 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
eastern Yakama Reservation, or near Sunnyside, moving east at 10
mph. Storm could intensify as it moves towards the east.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sunnyside, Grandview, Mabton, and Satus.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
